  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to report suspicious transactions to the appropriate authorities. Specific requirements can vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Identifying and documenting suspicious financial activities\n3. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n4. Conducting customer due diligence\n5. Maintaining transaction records\n\nProfessionals in banking, finance, legal, and other regulated sectors often have specific legal obligations to report potential money laundering activities.",
